title: Employment by economic sector in Sweden 2019
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 3 lines representing Agriculture, Industry, and Services. The y axis denotes Share of total employment and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall Agriculture, Industry, and Services are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The lines ordered according to average values of Share of total employment in descending order is: 1. Services, 2. Industry, and lastly, 3. Agriculture.
Throughout the period, Services generally had the highest Share of total employment relative to others with an average of 79.14, and it reached its maximum at 2019 with a value of 80.39.
After Services, Industry overall has the second highest values , with a mean value of 18.8, peaking at 2009.
Agriculture mostly had the least Share of total employment with a mean value of 1.97, which peaked at 2009 with a value of 2.18.
